    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. but i've seen people online saying the UN is basically just a broken system that gets in the way of actual sovereignty, like it just enables certain powers to do whatever they want through the security council. do historians see those kinds of criticisms as valid, or is that more of an outlier view?",
