      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "No, historians generally do not view the criticism of the UN as merely an outlier view; rather, it is a primary focus of scholarly critique regarding Security Council dynamics. Most research confirms that the P5 veto power allows major powers to shield their interests, often undermining the organization's unity and effectiveness. While some scholars argue this necessitates geopolitical reform to reclaim the UN's legitimacy, the consensus agrees that this systemic issue remains the organization's greatest structural weakness today.",
